<br>
“I made a promise to Thesus you’d return home in one piece. So watch yourself.” <br>
<br>
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp He turned storming off into the battlefield on the back of his black steed. His large grizzly bear staying next to Hippolyte incase of emergency. The bear offered her a bit more or protection not that she needed it of course. He turned his horse as the explosions sounded closer to him, his long hair whipping to the side from the forces.  Still charged head long towards the opposing side his teeth clenched together as he looked upon the hordes of enemy. His spear tip lowered towards the ground as he road on, the dogs that attacked him were soon impaled. He cast the spear aside once he had finished with the dogs near him. His horse leaping through the row on flames the god had created.   He pulled another spear, as he became one of the first in the charge hurling his weapon towards Poseidon. His hand reaching for another spear as he continued on.. <br>
