</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#6A74B4><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub11.ezboard.com/uthegreatapollo.showPublicProfile?language=EN>The Great Apollo</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Bronze Warrior</span><br>  Posts: 124<br> <font color=#FFFF00>(11/19/01 8:15:51 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> This too, shall pass</span><hr size=1> Apollo shook his head as he walked over to Aphrodite and Zephyr. His golden hair bounced back and forth as he shook his head. He placed a gaunleted hand upon both of their shoulders. He smiled his breath-taking smile and giggled a bit.<br>
<br>
&quot;A war is a war, just like a kiss is a kiss dearest Aphrodite. Both mean different things to different people. Both are expressions of passion. In many ways, Love is War. But do not work yourself into a huff, this too shall pass.&quot; he planted a kiss onto her scarlet cheek. He nodded to Zephyr and backed up, slowly turning around walking to his chariot. He comforted the horses, petting the muzzle.<br>
<br>
&quot;Run fast. No Fear&quot; he whispered into his horses ear. <br>
<br>
Off of a golden table he took his feathered helmet. Raising it slowly over his head he placed it on. It was snug, but it fit. He fixed his quiver over his shoulders, along with his bow. He sighed and picked up his sword, placing in its sheath upon his belt.<br>
<br>
He walked slowly over to his chariot and boarded it, the gates closing behind him. He grasped the reigns and whipped them quickly. Taking in a deep breathe he began to scream a battle-cry from the north. His horses bucked, and he raised his right fisted arm in a pre-decided triumph. The sun glistened off of his golden armor, it was as if Apollo was trapped in time in that moment, it looked like a fine painting. But the moment was soon over, there was no turning back. The chariot was racing into the midsts of the batte field.<br>
<br>
Several times he pulled back his arrows, sending them flying soundlessly through the air. The only sound Apollo heard was the sound of arrow hitting metal, and immedietly after, metal hitting flesh. Apollo reached back into his quiver and pulled from it another golden arrow. He signaled for his horses to run straight forward toward a soldier whose own chariot was flying like bat out of hell towards Apollo's. Apollo secured the arrow within the bow and pulled back, closing one eye and whispering:<br>
<br>
&quot;Shoot far. Shoot true.&quot;<br>
<br>
With that the arrow was sent sailing through the air in a deafening silence until the inevitable &quot;crack&quot; of the metal and &quot;thwap&quot; of the flesh.<br>
<br>
&quot;Damn it.&quot; Apollo uttered as he had missed the poor man's heart by a few inches. He would now have prolonged suffering, which is what Apollo tried to avoid by sending a death-blow to the heart. But he hadn't time to worry about such things now. He had a battle to fight.<br>
<br>
Apollo prepared another bow when something totally unexpected happened. He saw a spear hurdling towards his chariot. It struck. It was to late. The spear had wedged itself into the wheel of the chariot. The sound of cracking wood filled the air as Apollo found himself flying through the air.<br>
<br>
CRASH! He hit a tree. Apollo opened his eyes to find everything around him churning like the ocean. Grasping his head he removed his helmet. His eyes fell upon his assailent. Suddenly his vision was cured and he was filled with a vindictive rage like no other on the battlefield. Apollo set out for his attacker, without chariot and without helmet. He didn't care at this point, he saw and tasted blood.<br>
<br>
Many tried to stop him from reaching his goal, an officer of this joke of an army. But all they met was the unmerciful blade of his sword and the unpalatable taste of death. Apollo was seeing red as he stormed across the battlefield, taking down soldier after soldier. Finally he was eye to eye with his attacker.<br>
<br>
&quot;Ahahaha foolish Apollo! All &quot;Knowledgeable&quot; god of whining and a lot of NOTHING. You poor pointless little coddled mother's boy.&quot; a smirk rode across the man's bearded face. Arrogance shined in his eyes, the very breathes he took seemed to whisper &quot;arrogance&quot;. Apollo stood silent as he sized up his opponent and drew his sword once again, it covered in the blood of the man's kinsman.<br>
<br>
&quot;BING&quot; &quot;CHIME&quot; the sound of metal against metal filled the fields with the battling of Apollo and this nameless wonder. Apollo had been bested by the man several times, but Apollo was catching on. He must calm himself if he wished to vanquish this fiend. Apollo took a deep breathed and opened his mind. This was going to be over. Soon.<br>
<br>
The long metal blade came whistling down as Apollo just stepped out the way and slashed at the back of the man's knee's. The man fall to the ground screaming in pain. Apollo  grabbed him by the head and spoke out to those who could hear.<br>
<br>
&quot;BEFORE YOU IS A PRIME EXAMPLE...OF WHAT COMES TO THOSE WHO SHALL CHALLENGE THE GREAT APOLLO. MORE IMPORTANTLY, THIS IS WHAT SHALL COME TO THOSE WHO CHALLENGE THE AMAZON'S. DO HEED MY WARNING ON THIS DUSTY AFTERNOON AND CEASE THIS FOOLISHNESS, FOR CONTINUING IS POINTLESS.&quot;<br>
<br>
And with that Apollo raised his sword above his head and split the man's skull. Red. There was red everywhere. It was as if the ground around Apollo had been covered in apple peals, but it was the middle of November, no such things would happen. Blood. It tasted bitter-sweet as it dripped into Apollo's mouth, mixing with his own. He heaved for air. Vengence tasted sweet, victory even sweeter, but the man's blood was bitter as only the essense of a man with no morals could be.<br>
<br>
Apollo spit. He walked away from the split body covered in the man's blood. Drawing his sword he continued into the thickets of the battlefield. This was far from over. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#6A74B4><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub11.ezboard.com/umobellerophon.showPublicProfile?language=EN>MO Bellerophon</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_ball.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>registered user</span><br>  Posts: 32<br> <font color=#FFFF00>(11/19/01 9:25:22 pm)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://hometown.aol.com/alteredsoulsx/images/bellerophon-05.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> ... The Battle Began ...</span><hr size=1> Bellerophon watched as the amazons made the first move,his face was  stern underneath the mask he wore. He was almost hypnotized by the movements of both gods and amazons. He quickly snaps out of it as Pegasus shifts underneath him. He hadn't imagined there would be gods pitted against each other,but either way he wanted a piece of the action,for this battle would be a memorable one.<br>
<br>
Reaching to his right he grabs hold of his cross bow,and a silver pointed arrow.As he loads the arrow he whispers to Pegasus. &quot;Steady&quot; As Pegasus steadys himself he takes aim at a (nameless) amazon. He pulls back the trigger fireing the arrow which soars across the field until embedding deep into the chest of the amazon,the force of the arrow so strong,causing the amazon to jerk back instantly at contact and fall dead.<br>
<br>
A tight grin pulls on the corners of Bellerophons lips as he watches the impact of the arrow,he then places the cross bow back in its place,and pulls his sword out clutching it with his left hand,his right hand grasping Pegasus' reigns,he raises his sword into the air,at which point Pegasus Grunts and rears up,the steeds wings expanding fully.It was beautiful.But lasted only for a short moment as Pegasus flaps those large wings causing gusts of air to blow back anyone or anything that was in thier range.With each flap of those wings Pegasus pulled himself and his master into the air. With a nudge of his heels and a tug on the reigns Bellerophon directs Pegasus out into the battle.<br>
<br>
Soaring above the battle,Bellerophon peers down at the opposers,until his attention is directed to a brave amazon who had made it past the killer dogs and avenging gods. Pegasus hovers in one spot above the field,his wings continuously causing gusts of wind to blow back any oppresser or atleast hold them back for a time,but this one amazon managed to fight against the gust of air and swing her mighty sword fiercly at Bellerophon and his mount. Pegasus snorts and grunts as the grand steed swoops back away from the amazon,only to be nudged hard in the ribs and forced once again forward by his master. <br>
<br>
The sounds of metal against metal rang against Bellerophons ears as he blocked each of the amazons blows with his sword before finding an opening and drawing his sword back then quickly forward and across,taking the amazons head clean off her shoulders. The amazon promptly falling dead... <p>-=¤ Bellerophon ¤=-</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#6A74B4><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub11.ezboard.com/uqueenvaria.showPublicProfile?language=EN>QueenVaria</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>registered user</span><br>  Posts: 62<br> <font color=#FFFF00>(11/20/01 12:07:28 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: ... The Battle Began ...</span><hr size=1> Varia placed her bow on the saddle and exchanged it for her sword. Kicking her gelding she spurred him into action, taking off across the field, stomping out the last of the dogs on her way. She rode up beside Zelia and prepared to attack Hypnos. She didn't want to gang up, but since it was 16 to 5, she didn't really have a choice. <p><html> <font face="Signet Roundhand ATT"> Queen Varia </font> </html></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#6A74B4><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub11.ezboard.com/uqueenmaytha.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Queen Maytha</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>registered user</span><br>  Posts: 23<br> <font color=#FFFF00>(11/20/01 1:01:33 am)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://members.aol.com/amznqnmay/smallmaytha.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: ... The Battle Began ...</span><hr size=1> Maytha hears the wise words and start of the battle. She kicks her horse and her horse rushes down towards the enemies. As her horse goes, she pulls out 3 arrows, places it in her bow. She stops her horse, hope off and then aims. Shoots the arrows and it zooms thru the air aiming at the Gods. It hits