<br>
As Alastor heads his way Poseidon stands his ground and spreads his feet a little wider than shoulder width apart. His sandles dig into the ground and his muscles grow taught. His trident turns into a broad sword and a scabboard appears by right thigh. He places the sword into his scabboard quickly and keeping his eyes on Alastor takes a pitchers pose. His hands glow with menacing power and then like a baseball he throws a ball of green energy at Alastors steed. The attack continues as he leaves his hand outstretched, palm out, smaller balls of energy fly to the horse at blinding speeds.:: <p>Poseidon~Lord of the Deep Blue Sea~Patron Of Horses And Sailors~</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#6A74B4><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub11.ezboard.com/uvvvthegoddesshecatevvv.showPublicProfile?language=EN>VVV The Goddess Hecate VVV</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>registered user</span><br>  Posts: 74<br> <font color=#FFFF00>(11/20/01 3:05:25 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: ... The Battle Began ...</span><hr size=1> as her dragons pull her charriot high into the air they swoop down as a bow and arrow made of darkened steel appears in the tight grip of Hecate.  as she passes just a few feet above the ground she spots Apollo, pulling back the arrow tightly on the string she send the arrow wizzing past Apollos right ear into the eye  of an amazon fighting close by him. <br>
