Slender pale fingers clenched into fists at either side of her black glittering gown.  White teeth bit hard together under slim red lips, and icy blue eyes watched with anger as amazons fell.  Even if the male soldiers fell...it was nothing to be joyous over.  Her heart sunk as she could feel each amazon who breathed their last breath.  How dare her brother attack the amazons?!  What did Poseidon think he had to prove?  These women rarely went near the sea..and they were certainly not seafarers. <p>~~<<<<<<{{{{@</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#6A74B4><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub11.ezboard.com/uvvvthegoddesshecatevvv.showPublicProfile?language=EN>VVV The Goddess Hecate VVV</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>registered user</span><br>  Posts: 75<br> <font color=#FFFF00>(11/20/01 5:02:51 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: ~War~</span><hr size=1> Hecate let out a small raspy laugh as she saw Hera standing there with her fists clenched. not slowing down her rain of darkened steel arrows at Apollo she turned her head to watch the attack Poseidon was giving against the cursed amazons.<br>
